topNews.title: National Meeting, Public Procession Mark 110th Birth Anniversary of President Kim Il Sung in DPRK
content: A national meeting and a public procession of Pyongyang City took place with splendor at Kim Il Sung Square in Pyongyang on April 15, the 110th birth anniversary of the President.
Kim Jong Un, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and president of the State Affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, attended the events.

When the respected General Secretary appeared in the tribune of honor of the square amid the playing of the welcome music, all the participants raised stormy cheers of "Hurrah!" for him along with fireworks let off and balloons released.
He extended warm greeting to all the people celebrating the significant Day of the Sun with high political enthusiasm and proud labor successes, warmly waving back to the loudly cheering crowds.

The tribune of honor were taken by Choe Ryong Hae, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the WPK, first vice-president of the State Affairs Commission of the DPRK and chairman of the Standing Committee of the Supreme People's Assembly , Jo Yong Won, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau and secretary for Organizational Affairs of the WPK Central Committee, and Kim Tok Hun, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau of the WPK Central Committee, vice-president of the State Affairs Commission of the DPRK and premier of the Cabinet.

Among those at the tribune were senior officials of the Party and the government, directors and first vice-directors of departments of the WPK Central Committee, leading officials of the Cabinet, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, and officials and persons of merit who distinguished themselves in implementing the Party policies.
Ri Yong Gil, Kwon Yong Jin, Rim Kwang Il and other leading officials of the armed forces organs appeared at the tribune.

Present at the meeting were officials of the WPK Central Committee, officials of ministries and national institutions, service personnel of the Korean People's Army and the Public Security Forces, teaching staff and students of revolutionary schools, officials of institutions and industrial establishments and working people in Pyongyang.

Ri Il Hwan, member of the Political Bureau and secretary of the WPK Central Committee, made a report "The great Comrade Kim Il Sung's undying revolutionary history will be immortal along with the victorious advance of the cause of Juche".

The reporter recalled the noble revolutionary career of the President run through with the idea of believing in the people as in Heaven, saying that he dedicated himself to protecting the dignity and rights of the people and providing them with happiness, sharing his destiny with the people all his life. And the reporter noted that all the Korean people keep deeper in their hearts, despite shifts in generation, the truth that eternal victory and prosperity are in store for their country and the dignity, glory and happiness of the people are ensured, thanks to April 15, 1912, the birthday of the President.

He stressed it is a brilliant review of 110 years of Kim Il Sung's Korea that our country will demonstrate its might as the world's most powerful one perfectly embodying the ideal of its people in the face of any storm and stress when we add eternal brilliance to the greatest exploits performed by the President generation after generation and vigorously and invariably advance along the path of Juche paved by the President.

As there are encyclopedic revolutionary legacies representing the sacred careers of the President and Chairman Kim Jong Il and the tested guidance of the WPK Central Committee led by the respected Comrade Kim Jong Un, our state and people will always emerge victorious, he noted, appealing to the participants to make a dynamic advance to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche pioneered by the President and bring earlier the day when the ideal of the WPK, which regards it as the supreme principle of its activities to promote the wellbeing of the people, will be materialized perfectly.
After the national meeting the procession began.
A column of citizens holding a large flag of the Republic symbolic of their dignified state entered the square.
They were full of pride and confidence of having adorned every decade of the revolution with victories and glory, adding luster to their national flag century after century.

When a column of demonstrators escorting the cars carrying the statues of President Kim Il Sung and Chairman Kim Jong Il entered the square, fireworks were let off and numberless balloons were released.

Columns of workers, peasant dancers and others marched past the square, holding aloft the boards bearing such slogans as "Our socialist country built by the President!", "Legendary Chollima brought by the President!" and "Endless journey for people!"
The respected General Secretary acknowledged the cheers of the dependable people who remain faithful to their Party and state with single-minded loyalty and revolutionary spirit.

Such catchphrases symbolic of great history as "Independence in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliance in defence", "Chollima Korea" and "Path of Juche" were displayed on the square to represent the unshakable faith that only victory and glory are in store for the Korean people who are making a dauntless advance with firm confidence in justice and victory of their cause.

Columns of youth and students, service persons' families and persons of merit and children's union members showcased their strong aspiration to fulfill their duty and mission as the descendents of the President and soldiers and disciples of the Chairman by holding the President and the Chairman in high esteem as their eternal leaders and successfully accomplishing the cause of Juche under the uplifted banner of continuous revolution.

A column of demonstrators holding a large red flag bearing such catchphrases as "Powerful socialist country", "Single-hearted unity" and "Self-reliance" marched past the square to decorate the end of the procession, demonstrating the powerful spirit of the Korean people who are bringing earlier a new victory of revolution under the uplifted banner of our state-first principle, led by the respected General Secretary.
The respected General Secretary warmly waved back to cheering crowds.

The national meeting and the public procession of Pyongyang City fully demonstrated the revolutionary spirit and will of the Korean people to achieve the overall prosperity and development of Korean-style socialism by single-mindedly and devotedly upholding the leadership of the respected General Secretary.

topNews.title: Respected Comrade Kim Jong Un Visits Kumsusan Palace of Sun
content: All the people in the DPRK commemorates the 110th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung, whose august name shines in the nation's history spanning 5 000 years, as the great revolutionary event, holding him in high esteem as the eternal sun of socialist Korea. They extend the highest respects towards the sacred temple of Juche with ardent yearning for him that remains unchanged, no matter how much water may flow under the bridge.

Kim Jong Un, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK) and president of the State Affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), visited the Kumsusan Palace of the Sun together with his wife Ri Sol Ju on April 15, the Day of the Sun, the greatest auspicious holiday of the Korean nation.

Accompanying him were Choe Ryong Hae, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the WPK, first vice-president of the State Affairs Commission of the DPRK and chairman of the Standing Committee of the Supreme People's Assembly , Jo Yong Won, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau and secretary for Organizational Affairs of the WPK Central Committee, Kim Tok Hun, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau of the WPK Central Committee, vice-president of the State Affairs Commission of the DPRK and premier of the Cabinet, and other leading officials of the Party and the government, officials of the Party Central Committee, members of the Cabinet and leading officials of the working people's organizations.
Leading officials of the armed forces organs were present there.
Placed at the statues of President Kim Il Sung and Chairman Kim Jong Il was a floral basket from the respected Comrade Kim Jong Un.

Also laid before the statues were the floral baskets in the names of the WPK Central Committee, the State Affairs Commission of the DPRK, the Standing Committee of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK and the Cabinet of the DPRK.
The respected General Secretary and his wife, together with other visitors, paid high tribute to the statues of the great leaders.

At the halls where the President and the Chairman lie in state, the respected General Secretary and his wife made deep bows to the President and the Chairman as a token of their best wishes of immortality to the great leaders who built Korean-style socialism guided by the idea of believing in the people as in Heaven on this land, made the unprecedentedly glorious history of victory and miracles and laid the eternal foundations for ensuring the dignity and prosperity of posterity.

All the participants made a firm pledge to remain absolutely loyal to the idea and leadership of the respected General Secretary who adds eternal luster to the cause of the President and the Chairman and fulfill their heavy duty and responsibility entrusted with by the Party and the people by dedicating themselves to the sacred struggle for comprehensive development of socialist construction.

topNews.title: Pyongyang's New Landscape Symbolic of People-first Idea of WPK and Signal Development of Juche-oriented Architecture
content: Respected Comrade Kim Jong Un Cuts Ribbon at Inauguration Ceremony of Pothong Riverside Terraced Residential District

A distinctive terraced residential district has been built on a scenic bank of the Pothong River in Pyongyang, the capital city of the DPRK, amid ceaseless erection of monumental edifices symbolic of the development of civilization of Korean-style socialism under a grandiose plan for national prosperity unfolded at the 8th Congress of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK).

The Pothong Riverside Terraced Residential District, completed to bring about another dramatic change in Pyongyang, is a proud edifice of the new era that vividly represents the people-first idea of the Party Central Committee regarding it as its long-cherished desire to provide the people with the best material and cultural welfare in the world and its strategy for the development of Juche-oriented architecture.

The respected Comrade Kim Jong Un, who considers the people's laughter and happiness to be a criterion for assessing the national power, initiated the building of a luxurious residential district, which will serve as a fresh springboard for the country's architectural development, in order to present it to the persons of merit who contributed to the prosperity and development of the country. He personally organized and guided the whole process of its construction as a designer, owner and operator of the project.

The district, to which formative art, practicability and convenience are applied at the highest level, has taken its shape at a time-honored fine location in the center of the capital city under the warm care of the great Party Central Committee as a new model of housing construction and a world of fantasy in which people happily enjoy a new civilization of socialism.
An inauguration ceremony took place on April 13 with splendor.
Kim Jong Un, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and president of the State Affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, attended the ceremony.

Present there were Jo Yong Won, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau and secretary for Organizational Affairs of the WPK Central Committee, and Kim Tok Hun, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau of the WPK Central Committee, vice-president of the State Affairs Commission of the DPRK and premier of the Cabinet.

Also attending it were Ri Il Hwan, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, Kim Yong Hwan, chief secretary of the Pyongyang City Committee of the WPK, First Vice Department Director Ri Hi Yong and officials of the WPK Central Committee, officials of ministries and national institutions and Party and power organs in the capital city, those of the units involved in construction, builders, persons of merit and their family members who will move into Kyongru-dong, and other Pyongyangites.
When the respected General Secretary arrived at the ceremonial venue, the participants greeted him with thunderous cheers of "Hurrah!" amid a display of fireworks.

All the participants offered enthusiastic cheers to the respected General Secretary with profound reverence for him who makes indefatigable efforts to glorify the country as the world's best people's country, powerful and highly civilized, with his great love for the people and noble spirit of serving them.
The national anthem of the DPRK was solemnly played.
Jo Yong Won addressed the ceremony.

Referring to the great excitement at the emergence of a luxurious street under socialism, which epitomizes the Party Central Committee's noble outlook on the people, in a sacred site associated with the great leader's revolutionary life, Jo Yong Won stressed that it is the firm will of the Party Central Committee and the consistent policy of the government of the Republic to make the people supporting the Party and the state with their painstaking efforts enjoy the best civilization before anyone else would do, considering that their dedication of sweat and conscience to the sake of the country is more valuable than a thousand pieces of gold.

The completion of the Pothong Riverside Terraced Residential District intuitively shows that the day when everyone will enjoy a highly civilized and happy life is not far away in time, and further boosts the patriotic zeal, creativity and morale of all the people to spruce up their own houses by their own efforts, he noted.

Saying the owners of Kyongru-dong should continue to add glory to their worthwhile life as treasures of the country and standard-bearers of their collective, never forgetting the current excitement, he expressed belief that Kyongru-dong would be eternally admired as a residential area of genuine patriots dedicating their pure conscience and fervent enthusiasm to the prosperity of the country along with its elegant name.
The respected General Secretary cut the inaugural tape.

At that moment, thunderous cheers of "Hurrah!" reverberated throughout the ceremonial ground with fireworks set off and countless balloons released, gorgeously decorating the sky above the Pothong River where a new legend of love for the people in the era of the Workers' Party has been created.

This reflected the firm faith and will of all the participants to enjoy all victories and glories, a worthwhile life and a bright future in the course of single-mindedly and devotedly upholding the idea and leadership of the respected General Secretary, who confidently opens up a new world, a new era of a highly-civilized, prosperous and powerful country, by devoting himself to the sake of his beloved people, always placing them in his heart.
The respected General Secretary warmly waved back to the loudly cheering crowds.

A touching spectacle showing the great love for the people was witnessed at Kyongru-dong, every nook and cranny of which is filled with the boundless benevolence of the respected General Secretary who deems the working people's patriotic enthusiasm and sincere efforts priceless.

The respected General Secretary met and warmly congratulated the persons of merit, including Ri Chun Hi and Choe Song Won, chief announcers of the Central Broadcasting Committee of Korea, and Tong Thae Gwan, a member of the editorial board of the Rodong Sinmun, who were among the cheering crowds.

Holding hands of Ri Chun Hi making a deep bow to him as an expression of her deep gratitude for having received a marvelous dwelling house, he went to Block No. 7 of Kyongru-dong where she would live in.
Witnessing such a touching sight, in which the top leader of a country shares feelings with people, the participants in the event raised louder cheers.

Looking round the family room and other living rooms in her house, the respected General Secretary listened to the impressions of her family members with fatherly care and took a measure of benevolence so that the aged announcer would not feel any inconvenience while going up and down the stairs in her house.

The veteran announcer told him in excited tones that her house with all amenities is just like a hotel and all members of her family stayed up all night in tears of deep gratitude for the Party's benevolence.

Hearing her words in joy, the General Secretary said it is the sincerity of the Party that there is nothing to spare for the treasures of the country like her who has worked as a revolutionary announcer for the Party for more than 50 years since her girlhood. And he highly praised her for speaking to the world the voice of the Party and Juche Korea with youthful mettle and enthusiasm despite her age nearing eighty.

Noting that the veteran women announcers, whom the Party is proud of, are doing very important work of informing the world of the policies of the Party and the state and the prestige of the country, he placed deep trust on them, saying that they should not only achieve continuous successes in their job with ardent passion but also do their bit in training younger announcers who would shoulder the future of broadcasting.
Expressing expectation that she would as ever vigorously continue her work in good health as befitting a spokeswoman for the Party Central Committee, he had a photo taken with her family.
He also visited the houses of Choe Song Won and Tong Thae Gwan to warmly congratulate their families on moving into new houses before having photos taken with them.

Acknowledging the bows they repeatedly made in tears, gripped by profound gratitude, he told them that such phrase as a world for the people is not merely a slogan to our Party, in which a climate of unconditionally serving the people has been established, and our people, who firmly uphold their sovereignty with their own efforts, are the full-fledged owners who deserve a happy and highly civilized life.

He said that he misses President Kim Il Sung more than ever before as a luxurious residential district has been built at a site associated with the President's revolutionary life on the occasion of the significant Day of the Sun.

Stressing that it is a filial duty and noble obligation of the descendents of the President to live up to his expectations, the respected General Secretary said that our Party, true to the intention of the President, built a fine street for the people whom he had loved so much all his life and he would have been satisfied to see the cozy dwellings built for the patriots and persons of merit in the place where his residence had once located.

Warmly holding the hands of persons of merit who were following him step by step, reluctant to be away from him, he repeatedly wished them a happy future and promised them that he would make time to visit their houses again in the future.
After the ceremony Pyongyangites looked around the dwellings with their owners.

Looking at the palatial dwelling houses with all amenities in admiration, they keenly realized the noble intention and warm benevolence of the Party Central Committee which set the construction for the happiness of the people as a far-sighted patriotic work for bringing about a future of high civilization.

They hardened their confidence in the future of the country which will turn brighter under the leadership of the great Party in the residential district where the Juche-oriented and popular characters peculiar to our Party and state, Korean-style charms and features and the development trend of modern architecture are successfully embodied.

The Pothong Riverside Terraced Residential District, a new scenery of Pyongyang symbolizing the great era of Kim Jong Un, will shine as an edifice representing Korean-style civilization, demonstrating the people-first idea of the Party believing in the people as in Heaven and the indomitable spirit of socialist Korea which is making leaping progress on the great strength of self-reliance.

topNews.title: Monumental Edifice Symbolic of New Turn in Promotion of Korean-style Socialist Civilization
content: Inauguration Ceremony of Songhwa Street Held with Splendor
Respected Comrade Kim Jong Un Cuts Inaugural Tape

An ideal street for the people has been erected majestically in Songsin and Songhwa areas of the capital city of Pyongyang to demonstrate the high spirit and remarkable creativity of the Korean people, who are vigorously advancing toward the brighter future of Korean-style socialism under the leadership of the great Workers' Party of Korea (WPK), and to represent the rapid development of the country dashing toward the attainment of a grandiose goal.

Songhwa Street, built in the eastern gateway to Pyongyang under the unique architectural development plan of the Party Central Committee and the plan for building 50 000 flats in Pyongyang set forth at the 8th Congress of the Party, is an outcome of the WPK's long-cherished desire to provide the people with more stable and civilized living conditions and successfully resolve the housing shortage of capital citizens. The street is, at the same time, the first entity symbolic of the new era of comprehensive development seething with great creation and changes.

True to the high intention of the Party Central Committee to turn Pyongyang better into the center of disseminating the Juche idea, Juche-oriented culture and Korean-style high civilization and into the great city of the people, the soldiers and civilians involved in the project performed an eye-opening miracle of building the distinctive grand architectural group of 10 000 flats, including an 80-storeyed skyscraper, within a year by waging a strenuous onward campaign, the fierce 24/7 struggle, despite manifold challenges and trials.

Through the construction of the street which opened a new turning point of development in the capital city construction, our people and servicepersons fully demonstrated the validity of the Party's Juche-oriented idea on architectural beauty, the potentiality of the self-supporting economy and the irresistible might of the single-hearted unity of the Party and the masses and vividly showed the true picture of Korean-style socialism vigorously advancing toward the bright future.
An inauguration ceremony of the street was held with splendor on Monday.
Kim Jong Un, general secretary of the WPK and president of the State Affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, attended the ceremony.
When he arrived at the ceremonial venue, fireworks were set off and the participants broke into thunderous cheers of "Hurrah!"

All the participants cheered enthusiastically as a token of their deep reverence for the respected General Secretary Kim Jong Un who set the people-first principle as the eternal political idea and unshakable political mode of the WPK and has dedicated himself to building an ideal socialist society brimming with the laughter and happiness of the people.

Present at the ceremony were Jo Yong Won, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau and secretary for Organizational Affairs of the WPK Central Committee, and Kim Tok Hun, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau of the WPK Central Committee, vice-president of the State Affairs Commission of the DPRK and premier of the Cabinet.

Also attending it were Ri Il Hwan, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, Kim Yong Hwan, chief secretary of the Pyongyang City Committee of the WPK, members of the headquarters for the construction of 50 000 flats in Pyongyang, officials from Party and power organs in the capital city, soldier- and civilian-builders and Pyongyangites.
The participants also included the working people, students and children who are to live in the new street of the people successfully completed under the leadership of the WPK.

The ceremonial ground was filled with absolute trust and fervent admiration for the Party Central Committee that vigorously leads the people to a new era of creation and miracles, bringing all their dreams and ideals into brilliant fruition.
The national anthem of the DPRK was solemnly played.
Kim Tok Hun addressed the ceremony.

There are many splendid inauguration ceremonies recorded in our Republic's history of grand construction for promoting the well-being of the people but this event is associated with many touching stories that are really unforgettable and should not be forgotten, the speaker said, adding that the Songhwa area is the monument to the great love which was erected by the strong faith that the things desired and anticipated by the people must be done without fail in any situation.

He expressed belief that the Pyongyangites moving into new houses amid the blessings of the whole country would always remember this eventful moment and dedicate their all to the prosperity of the country.
The respected Comrade Kim Jong Un cut the inauguration tape.

Fireworks were let off and balloons released and all the participants raised stormy cheers of "Hurrah!" with deep gratitude to the respected General Secretary who builds a land of bliss for the people with his warm love, repeatedly showing great benevolence for them.
The respected General Secretary warmly waved back to them, wishing them happiness in a new street and new houses.

The ground of the inaugural ceremony was flooded with the great excitement of the capital citizens, who could hardly repress their deep gratitude to the tender-hearted father for his benevolence as warm as sunlight in spring, looking up to him with tears in their eyes.
The respected General Secretary warmly waved back to the cheering crowds for a long time, sincerely wishing our people a happy and highly civilized life in their modern dwellings.
At the end of the ceremony, Party and government cadres looked around the street.

Seeing the imposing 80-storeyed sky-scraper, an elevated bridge, public catering facilities, they more keenly realized that every moment and day spent for putting great ideas into practice by the respected General Secretary, who continues his journey of devoted service for the people, unhesitatingly going through thick and thin for their sake, have resulted in providing the cornerstone of the country's prosperity and adding glory to the new era of the Workers' Party when the whole country is overflowing with the people's happiness.

Walking along the new street symbolic of high civilization, the blessed citizens unanimously said our Party, state, world and policy are the best, out of their irrepressible gratitude toward the motherly Party which willingly burdens itself for the sake of the people with a heavy duty in the harshest-ever time.

More deeply realizing the immutable truth that victory, glory, happiness and a rosy future are in store for them when they firmly trust and follow the respected General Secretary, they firmly pledged to take the lead in creating new things and making innovations and become the performers of feats in the honorable and proud struggle for the prosperity and development of the country.

Songhwa Street, which has been erected by the noble intention of the WPK that confidently brings earlier a new world and era of a prosperous and powerful nation under the uplifted banner of "The People Are God", the single-minded unity and self-reliance, will shine forever as a monument to the warm love for the people in the great era of Kim Jong Un along with the rosy morrow of the capital city of Pyongyang which will be transformed into a more magnificent city.

topNews.title: Respected Comrade Kim Jong Un Inspects Pothong Riverside Terraced Residential District
content: Kim Jong Un, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and president of the State Affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, inspected the Pothong Riverside Terraced Residential District built in Kyongru-dong, Central District.

Accompanying him were Jo Yong Won, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau and secretary for Organizational Affairs of the WPK Central Committee, Ri Hi Yong, first vice-department director of the WPK Central Committee, and Kim Yo Jong, Hyon Song Wol and Kim Yong Su, vice-department directors of the WPK Central Committee.
The respected Comrade Kim Jong Un was greeted by leading officials of the designing organ and construction unit in field.

The terraced residential district built in Kyongru-dong in a unique way will be homes of working people including labor innovators in various fields, persons of distinguished services, scientists, educators and writers who devote themselves to the Party and the state, reflective of the loving care of Kim Jong Un.

Kim Jong Un, who pays special attention to the provision of more affluent and wonderful living conditions to our people and signal development of the level of civilization in the capital city and the Juche-oriented architecture, mapped out a plan for building a special residential district by harmoniously arranging terraced, many-storied and low-storied dwelling houses and facilities for public service in the best place on the bank of the Pothong River flowing across the city center, a year ago. He then examined a lot of designs and layouts over the past one year and solved every problem arising in the construction with his energetic guidance.

The residential district of unique form built under the direct guidance of Kim Jong Un has successfully been completed to provide the residents with the maximum convenience for their living. Luxury dwelling houses have been built in good harmony with the surrounding environment, and landscaping in the area been improved. As a result, the level of the civilization in the city and scenery of the Pothong riverside have undergone a radical change.

Going around the district for a long time, he said that the builders made a lot of efforts to implement the Party's decision in the past one year, true to the Party's policy on construction, and that a model residential district of new form to which our Party's idea on architectural beauty has been thoroughly applied and wonderful combination of modernity and convenience are ensured was created in the central part of the capital city thanks to the ardent loyalty and labor efforts of the builders.
He said with satisfaction that the Party Central Committee is very pleased over it.

He stressed repeatedly that the experience gained in building the new model residential district in Kyongru-dong is of very important significance in carrying out the immediate task for construction in Pyongyang and in provinces put forward by our Party under its plan to build dwelling houses extensively across the country.

He called on designing institutions at all levels in Pyongyang and in provinces to keep making exertions to widely introduce standard, achievements and experience gained in such architectural and landscaping designs, and further develop the level of designing theory for all fields to meet the daily increasing demand of our people in living.

The designing institutions and educational organizations at all levels need to focus on making the detailed examination of the world level in landscaping designing in particular and actively introducing landscaping standard and methods to suit to the specific conditions of our country and taking decisive measures for establishing and developing in a unique way the landscaping designing theory of our own style.

He underscored the need for the urban management field and relevant units including designing institutions to take strong measures so as to give scientific and theoretical precedence to landscaping designing for improving the environment in the capital city and seats of provinces, cities and counties across the country, and to do landscaping in the development-oriented way in conformity with the natural and geographical features of relevant regions and with the modern trend.

He gave important teachings about the strategy for the development of the Juche architecture, noting that the construction is an important political work of increasing the overall power of the country and leading our people to socialist civilization of our own style.
He learned about the construction, looking round interior of dwellings of various styles for hours.
Saying that the interior of the houses are convenient for the living of people, he was so pleased to provide again our working people with more wonderful houses.
He told officials to hand over entrance certificates to those selected in various fields and hold significant completion ceremony before the significant Day of the Sun.

All the officials and builders were full of firm pledge to perform greater miracles and innovations with soaring spirit to lead the world in the worthwhile endeavors of building a civilized powerful country, bearing in mind the patriotic devotion of great efforts made by the respected Comrade Kim Jong Un for the prosperity of the country and happiness of the people.
